# ── Maps (FREE — no API key needed) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# OpenFreeMap tiles   → https://openfreemap.org  (completely free, no signup)
# OSRM routing        → https://project-osrm.org (free public demo server)
# Nominatim geocoding → https://nominatim.org    (free, 1 req/sec limit)
# No environment variables needed for any of these.

# ── Weather (FREE — no API key needed) ────────────────────────────────────────
# Open-Meteo → https://open-meteo.com (completely free, no signup)
# No environment variable needed.

# ── Auth (FREE via Supabase built-in) ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Magic link email auth uses Supabase's built-in SMTP (free, 3 emails/hour on free tier)
# For higher volume: add SendGrid free tier (100 emails/day free)
# SMTP settings → Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → Email Templates

# ── Push Notifications (FREE via Expo, no EAS needed for dev) ─────────────────
# expo-notifications works with Expo Go for testing without any EAS account.
# For production builds you need EAS (free tier available):
# EXPO_PUBLIC_EAS_PROJECT_ID=your_project_id_from_eas_init

# ── Discord Integration (optional, FREE bot API) ──────────────────────────────
# Create bot at https://discord.com/developers/applications
# DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=your_bot_token
# DISCORD_GUILD_ID=your_server_id

# ── Summary: what you actually need to fill in ────────────────────────────────
# Required for full functionality:
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL       ← from Supabase dashboard
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY  ← from Supabase dashboard
#
# Everything else (maps, routing, geocoding, weather) works with NO keys.
